o}} | A [[Chernetidae|chernetid]] [[pseudoscorpion]]. The type species is ''Mayachernes maatiatus''. Judson (2016) considered genus ''Mayachernes'' to be a junior synonym of the genus ''[[Byrsochernes]]'', though he maintained ''M. maatiatus'' as a distinct species within the latter genus.<ref>{{Cite journal|author =Mark L.I. Judson |year=2016 |title=Pseudoscorpions (Arachnida, Chelonethi) in Mexican amber, with a list of extant species associated with mangrove and ''Hymenaea'' trees in Chiapas |journal=Boletín de la Sociedad Geológica Mexicana |volume=68 |issue=1 |pages=57–79 |url=http://boletinsgm.igeolcu.unam.mx/bsgm/index.php/component/content/article/292-sitio/articulos/cuarta-epoca/6801/1434-6801-8-judson }}</ref> | |- | ''[[Minyacarus]]''<ref name=TriassicmitesJSP /> | Gen. et sp. nov | Valid<ref name=TriassicmitesJSPZB /> | Sidorchuk & Lindquist ''in'' Sidorchuk ''et al.'' | Late Triassic (Carnian) | | {{Flag|Italy}} | A [[mite]] of the [[Tetrapodili]] lineage. The type species is ''Minyacarus aderces''. | |- | ''[[Montsecarachne]]''<ref>{{cite journal |author =Paul A. Selden |year=2014 |title=A new spider (Araneae: Haplogynae: Plectreuridae) from the Cretaceous Fossil-Lagerstätte of El Montsec, Spain |journal=Journal of Arachnology |volume=42 |issue=1 |pages=16–23 |doi=10.1636/B13-51.1 }}</ref> | Gen. et sp. nov | Valid | Selden | Early Cretaceous (c. 129 Ma) | El Montsec | {{Flag|Spain}} | A [[plectreurid spider]]. The type species is ''Montsecarachne amicus''. | |- | ''[[Opilioacarus groehni|?Opilioacarus groehni]]''<ref>{{cite journal |author =Jason A. Dunlop and Leopoldo Ferreira de Oliveira Bernardi |year=2014 |title=An opilioacarid mite in Cretaceous Burmese amber |journal=Naturwissenschaften |volume=101 |issue=9 |pages=759–763 |doi=10.1007/s00114-014-1212-0 |pmid=25027588}}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid | Dunlop & Bernardi | Late Cretaceous (Cenomanian) | Burmese amber | {{Flag|Myanmar}} | An [[Opilioacarida|opilioacarid]] [[mite]] found in Burmese amber, 