oida]]n [[Isopoda|isopod]]. The type species is ''Cymothoidana websteri''. | |- | ''Cypria poietes<ref name=NorthFalklandBasin /> | Sp. nov | Valid | Ayress & Whatley | Early Cretaceous | | South [[Atlantic Ocean]] (North [[Falkland Islands|Falkland]] Basin) | A non-marine [[ostracod]], a species of ''[[Cypria (genus)|Cypria]]''. | |- | ''[[Cytheropteron paramassoni]]<ref name=JP884deepseaostracods>{{Cite journal|author1=Moriaki Yasuhara |author2=Hisayo Okahashi |year=2014 |title=Quaternary deep-sea ostracode taxonomy of Ocean Drilling Program Site 980, eastern North Atlantic Ocean |journal=Journal of Paleontology |volume=88 |issue=4 |pages=770–785 |doi=10.1666/13-125 }}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid | Yasuhara & Okahashi | Late Quaternary | | North [[Atlantic Ocean]] ([[Rockall Plateau]]) | A [[Cytheruridae|cytherurid]] [[Podocopida|podocopid]] [[ostracod]], a species of ''[[Cytheropteron]]''. | |- | ''[[Damonella|Damonella grandiensis]]''<ref name=CR48ostracods /> | Sp. nov | Valid | Tomé, Lima Filho & Neumann | Early Cretaceous | Araripe basin | {{Flag|Brazil}} | An [[ostracod]]. | |- | ''[[Dawsonius tigris]]<ref name=BMFMSmudshrimpsPawpawFm /> | Sp. nov | Valid | Frantescu | Early Cretaceous (Albian) | [[Paw Paw Formation]] | {{Flag|United States}} | A member of [[Axiidea]] belonging to the family [[Ctenochelidae]], a species of ''[[Dawsonius]]''. | |- | ''[[Devonostenopus]]<ref>{{Cite journal|author1=Wade T. Jones |author2=Rodney M. Feldmann |author3=Carrie E. Schweitzer |author4=Frederick R. Schram |author5=Rose-Anna Behr |author6=Kristen L. Hand |year=2014 |title=The first Paleozoic stenopodidean from the Huntley Mountain Formation (Devonian–Carboniferous), north-central Pennsylvania |journal=Journal of Paleontology |volume=88 |issue=6 |pages=1251–1256 |doi=10.1666/13-059 }}</ref> | Gen. et sp. nov | Valid | Jones ''et al.'' | Devonian | [[Huntley Mountain Formation]] | {{Flag|United States}} | A member of [[Stenopodidea]]. The type species is ''Devonostenopus penn