as>{{Cite journal|author1=H. Kato |author2=R. Nakashima |author3=Y. Yanagisawa |year=2014 |title=Two new Early Pliocene species of the crab genus ''Hyas'' Leach, 1814 (Majoidea, Oregoniidae) from northeast Japan |journal=Scripta Geologica |volume=147 |pages=269–287 |url=http://www.scriptageologica.nl/16/nr147/a20 }}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid | Kato, Nakashima & Yanagisawa | Early Pliocene | [[Chippubetsu Formation]] | {{Flag|Japan}} | A member of [[Oregoniidae]], a species of ''[[Hyas (genus)|Hyas]]''. | |- | ''[[Hyas tentokujiensis]]<ref name=SGPlioceneHyas /> | Sp. nov | Valid | Kato, Nakashima & Yanagisawa | Early Pliocene | [[Tentokuji Formation]] | {{Flag|Japan}} | A member of [[Oregoniidae]], a species of ''[[Hyas (genus)|Hyas]]''. | |- | ''[[Icenilepas]]<ref name=PGAcirripedes /> | Gen. et sp. nov | Valid | Gale | Late Cretaceous (Santonian) | | {{Flag|United Kingdom}} | A [[Zeugmatolepadidae|zeugmatolepadid]] [[barnacle]]. The type species is ''Icenilepas collinsi''. | |- | ''Ilhasina? leiodermatus<ref name=NorthFalklandBasin /> | Sp. nov | Valid | Ayress & Whatley | Early Cretaceous | | South [[Atlantic Ocean]] (North [[Falkland Islands|Falkland]] Basin) | A non-marine [[ostracod]], possibly a species of ''[[Ilhasina]]''. | |- | ''[[Ilyocypris bisulcata]]<ref>{{Cite journal|author1=Haiying Qu |author2=Dangpeng Xi |author3=Sha Li |author4=Jean Paul Colin |author5=Qinghua Huang |author6=Xiaoqiao Wan |year=2014 |title=Late Cretaceous–early Paleocene ostracod biostratigraphy of Scientific Drilling Sk1(N) in the Songliao Basin, northeast China |journal=Journal of Paleontology |volume=88 |issue=4 |pages=786–798 |doi=10.1666/13-076 }}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid | Qu ''et al.'' | Early [[Paleocene]] | [[Mingshui Formation]] | {{Flag|China}} | An [[Ilyocyprididae|ilyocypridid]] [[Cypridoidea|cypridoid]] [[ostracod]], a species of ''[[Ilyocypris]]''. | |- | ''[[Italianira]]<ref name=JCBRaninoida /> | Gen. et comb. nov | Valid | Karasawa ''et al.'' | Eocene (Ypresian) | | 