79}}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid | Archibald, Kehlmaier & Mathewes | Ypresian | [[Klondike Mountain Formation]] | {{Flag|United States}} | A [[Pipunculidae|pipunculid]] [[fly]], a species of ''Metanephrocerus''. | [[File:Metanephrocerus belgardeae SR 08-06-02 01.jpg|thumb|center|150px|''[[Metanephrocerus belgardeae]]'']] |- | ''[[Metanephrocerus|Metanephrocerus groehni]]<ref name="Kehlmair2014">{{cite journal |last1=Kehlmaier |first1=C |last2=Dierick |first2=M |last3=Skevington |first3=JH |year=2014 |title=Micro-CT studies of amber inclusions reveal internal genitalic features of big-headed flies, enabling a systematic placement of ''Metanephrocerus'' Aczel, 1948 (Insecta: Diptera: Pipunculidae) |journal=Arthropod Systematics & Phylogeny |volume=72 |issue=1 |pages=23–36}}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid | Kehlmaier & Skevington | [[Priabonian]] | [[Baltic amber]] | {{Flag|Russia}} | A [[Pipunculidae|pipunculid]] [[fly]], a species of ''Metanephrocerus''. | |- | ''[[Metanephrocerus|Metanephrocerus hoffeinsorum]]<ref name="Kehlmair2014"/> | Sp. nov | Valid | Kehlmaier & Skevington | [[Priabonian]] | [[Baltic amber]] | {{Flag|Russia}} | A [[Pipunculidae|pipunculid]] [[fly]], a species of ''Metanephrocerus''. | |- | ''[[Microphorites magaliae]]''<ref>{{Cite journal|author1=Vincent Perrichot |author2=Michael S. Engel |year=2014 |title=Youngest occurrence of the genus ''Microphorites'' (Diptera: Dolichopodidae): A new species in Late Cretaceous Vendean amber |journal=Paleontological Contributions |volume=10G |pages=30–33 |url=http://hdl.handle.net/1808/15987 }}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid | Perrichot & Engel | Late Cretaceous (middle Cenomanian to early Santonian, 97–85 Ma) | | {{Flag|France}} | A member of [[Dolichopodidae]], a species of ''[[Microphorites]]''. | |- | ''[[Nannotanyderus|Nannotanyderus oliviae]]<ref>{{Cite journal|author1=Kornelia Skibińska |author2=Wiesław Krzemiński |author3=Robert A. Coram |year=2014 |title=Discovery of the most ancient member of family Tanyderidae (D