olica''. | |- | ''[[Eohypolestes]]<ref name=IsleWightodonatans /> | Gen. et sp. nov | Valid | Nel & Fleck | Late Eocene | | {{Flag|United Kingdom}} | A [[damselfly]] related to the genus ''[[Hypolestes]]''. The type species is ''Eohypolestes hooleyi''. | |- | ''[[Eolestes|Eolestes ramosus]]<ref name=ZT38872>{{Cite journal|author1=Dale E. Greenwalt |author2=Günter Bechly |year=2014 |title=A re-description of the fossil damselfly ''Eolestes syntheticus'' Cockerell, 1940 (Odonata: Zygoptera: Eolestidae n. fam.) with description of new taxa from the Eocene of North America |journal=Zootaxa |volume=3887 |issue=2 |pages=138–156 |doi=10.11646/zootaxa.3887.2.2 }}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid | Greenwalt & Bechly | Eocene | [[Kishenehn Formation]] | {{Flag|United States}} | An [[Eolestidae|eolestid]] [[damselfly]], a species of ''Eolestes''. | |- | ''[[Eomacrodiplax]]<ref name=IsleWightodonatans /> | Gen. et sp. nov | Valid | Nel & Fleck | Late Eocene | | {{Flag|United Kingdom}} | A [[dragonfly]] related to the genus ''[[Urothemis]]''. The type species is ''Eomacrodiplax incompleta''. | |- | ''[[Juraheterophlebia|Juraheterophlebia sinica]]''<ref>{{Cite journal|author1=André Nel |author2=Dany Azar |author3=Di-ying Huang |year=2014 |title=A new Middle Jurassic Chinese fossil clarifies the systematic composition of the Heterophlebioptera (Odonata: Trigonoptera) |journal=Alcheringa: An Australasian Journal of Palaeontology |volume=38 |issue=1 |pages=130–134 |doi=10.1080/03115518.2014.843385 }}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid | Nel, Azar & Huang | Middle Jurassic | | {{Flag|China}} | A member of [[Odonata]] and [[Heterophlebioptera]], a species of ''Juraheterophlebia''. | |- | ''[[Lestes dianacompteae]]<ref>{{Cite journal|author =Arturo Compte-Sart |year=2014 |title=Nueva especie del género ''Lestes'' Leach, 1815 (Insecta, Odonata) del Mioceno de Bellver de Cerdanya (Lérida) |journal=Graellsia |volume=70 |issue=1 |pages=e001 |doi=10.3989/graellsia.2014.v70.097 }}</ref> | Sp. nov | Valid<ref>h