{{short description|Place where the Anatolian Plate, the Eurasian Plate and the Arabian Plate meet}}
[[File:Anatolian Plate.png|thumb|The Karlıova Triple Junction at the junction of the East and North Anatolian Faults|320px]]

The '''Karlıova Triple Junction''' is a geologic [[triple junction]] of three [[tectonic]] plates: the [[Anatolian Plate]], the [[Eurasian Plate]] and the [[Arabian Plate]].

The Karlıova Triple Junction is found where the east-west trending [[North Anatolian Fault]] intersects the [[East Anatolian Fault]] coming up from the southwest. Because each arm of the junction is a transform fault (F), the Karlıova Triple Junction is an F-F-F type junction.{{clarify|reason=Not clear how a FFF junction is geometrically possible|date=October 2018}}}

